      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "A small field, but a good contest. DURAZZO (3) was looking to make it four Listed wins on the trot in the Thomas Lyons Stakes at Hobart when he was beaten a whisker over 1400m by STEPARTY. Didn't have the best of luck and should enjoy a softer run here. Was backed off the map winning over this distance prior and he can turn the tables. STEPARTY (1) stormed home to win that contest as favourite and under John Allen is sure to be putting in the big strides late again. He's feared. CARTOON GRAVEYARD (4) spiked his figures beaten 1.5L in the same race. It was a big effort after settling back from the awkward barrier. He will in closer contact here and deserves consideration. Ditto JUST CRUISIN' (5) who finished a lip behind the above off a near miss in the Inevitable Stakes.",
